  npcVisitFlavors:
  - recounts a route you would never find on your own.
  - names three towns past the ridge and says what each is worth visiting.
  - traces something in the dirt that might be a map, then scuffs it out.
  npcExchangeFlavors:
  - tucks a fistful of berries into your kit. Road food. Don't make a ceremony of it.
  - hands you a tally stick, carved with distances you don't quite recognize.
  buildingDilapidatedName: Overgrown Waypost
  buildingDilapidatedColor: {r: 0.42, g: 0.4, b: 0.32, a: 1}
  buildingStages:
  - displayName: Waypost
    verb: clear
    material: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 961a0538cbaf46f9a43f9aea11b18552, type: 2}
    costPerTick: 2
    progressCost: 4
    requiredSpecialization: 
    tint: {r: 0.65, g: 0.62, b: 0.5, a: 1}
  - displayName: Mark the Route
    verb: mark
    material: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 1066a13ea81de794aa4f4ff5491bcebc, type: 2}
    costPerTick: 2
    progressCost: 4
    requiredSpecialization: herald
    tint: {r: 0.75, g: 0.72, b: 0.58, a: 1}
  buildingRestoredFlavors:
  - stands as a quiet waypoint, recognized by those who know to look.
  - hums with a traveler's kind of life, never quite settled, never quite gone.
